      "timestep_posted": 37
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six. This M96/03 powerplant utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift, delivering a linear power band through the 6-speed Getrag G96 manual transaxle. The chassis maintains excellent torsional rigidity, supported by a McPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension setup that provides exceptional kinematic feedback. This unit has undergone an IMS bearing retrofit and a Rear Main Seal (RMS) replacement, addressing critical failure points. The hydraulic power steering remains communicative, and the four-piston Monobloc calipers provide consistent deceleration with minimal fade. While the exterior shows minor stone chips consistent with a 'good' condition rating, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response are sharp, making this an ideal candidate for a purist seeking analog engagement.",
